**ScrivenerSync**

Beta Reader Platform

*Business Domain Model — Phase 1  |  Version 3*

# **1. Purpose and Scope**

This document defines the business domain model for Phase 1 of the ScrivenerSync Beta Reader Platform. It specifies all entities, their properties and relationships, the business rules governing them, the domain services that operate on them, and the invariants that must always hold. It is implementation-agnostic and intended as the reference from which a test-driven C# solution will be constructed.

Version 3 extends the model to support full multi-tenancy. Each author operates an independent Tenancy — their own isolated workspace containing their own projects, readers, and data. A single Account (login identity) may own one Tenancy and simultaneously hold reader membership in any number of other authors' Tenancies. No data crosses Tenancy boundaries.

The system is deployment-independent. It targets no specific cloud provider, hosting platform, or operating system. It runs wherever .NET runs. All external dependencies — email delivery, file system access, Dropbox integration, database — are accessed through abstract interfaces with concrete implementations supplied by configuration. No platform-specific SDKs are referenced in the domain or application layers.

Phase 1 scope: the system reads a Scrivener project from a Dropbox-synced folder registered per Tenancy, allows an author to publish sections for review, allows authenticated beta readers to comment on those sections in threaded conversations, tracks reading progress, delivers email notifications, and allows the author to respond. No write-back to Scrivener is in scope for Phase 1.

# **2. Actors**

| **Actor** | **Description** | **Scope** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Author | An Account that owns a Tenancy. Has full visibility of all content and comments within their Tenancy, including private ones. May activate and deactivate projects, publish sections, manage reader memberships, and respond to any comment thread. Exactly one Author (Owner) per Tenancy. | Per Tenancy |
| Beta Reader | An Account holding a Membership in a Tenancy. May read published sections on the reader-active project within that Tenancy. May create and participate in comment threads. May configure personal notification preferences per Tenancy. The same Account may be a Beta Reader in multiple Tenancies simultaneously. | Per Tenancy |
| System | The automated background process. Watches each Tenancy's registered Dropbox connection, parses Scrivener projects, keeps section trees in sync, and dispatches email notifications. | Platform-wide |
| Platform | The operator of the ScrivenerSync service. Manages Account existence. No role within any individual Tenancy. | Platform-wide |

# **3. Entities**

## **3.1 Account**

Represents the platform-wide identity of any person using the system. An Account exists independently of any Tenancy. Credentials, display name, and platform-level soft-deletion are held here. An Account may own at most one Tenancy and may hold reader Memberships in any number of other Tenancies.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **Email** | Primary login credential. Must be unique across all Accounts on the platform. Verified implicitly when the Account holder first accepts any invitation or activates their owned Tenancy. |
| **DisplayName** | Name shown in the UI alongside comments, platform-wide. Set by the Account holder. Immutable by any Tenancy; changes propagate immediately across all Tenancies and all historical comments. |
| **PasswordHash** | Hashed credential. Set on first activation. May be changed by the Account holder. |
| **IsSoftDeleted** | Boolean. Set true when the Account holder permanently removes their own account. Affects all Tenancy memberships simultaneously. No data is physically removed. |
| **SoftDeletedAt** | Timestamp of platform-level soft deletion. Null if never deleted. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of Account creation. |
| **LastLoginAt** | Timestamp of most recent successful login across any Tenancy. Null until first login. |

## **3.2 Tenancy**

Represents the isolated workspace belonging to one author. All projects, sections, comments, and reader memberships are scoped to a Tenancy. A Tenancy is created when an author registers on the platform. Financial obligations attach to the Tenancy via the Account that owns it.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **Name** | Human-readable name for the Tenancy (e.g. the author's pen name or studio name). Set by the owner. |
| **OwnerAccountId** | Foreign key to Account. The Account that owns this Tenancy. Immutable after creation. Exactly one per Tenancy. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of Tenancy creation. |
| **IsSoftDeleted** | Boolean. Set true when the owner closes their Tenancy. Hides all content from readers and suspends all processing. No data is physically removed. |
| **SoftDeletedAt** | Timestamp of soft deletion. Null if not deleted. |

## **3.3 TenancySubscription**

Records the subscription tier and billing status for a Tenancy. One record per Tenancy. Billing execution is handled by an external provider; this entity holds the tier assignment and the external reference required to enforce limits and surface status. Financial obligation rests with the Account identified as Tenancy owner.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. One-to-one. |
| **Tier** | Enumeration: Free, Paid, Ultimate. Developer-assigned for Phase 1. |
| **ExternalReferenceId** | Reference identifier from the external billing provider. Null if no external billing record exists (e.g. Free tier). |
| **Status** | Enumeration: Active, Suspended, Cancelled. Suspension and cancellation are signalled by the external billing system. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of subscription record creation. |
| **UpdatedAt** | Timestamp of most recent status or tier change. |

## **3.4 TenancyMembership**

Represents the relationship between an Account and a Tenancy, carrying the Account's role within that Tenancy. An Account holds exactly one TenancyMembership per Tenancy. The Owner membership (Role = Author) is created when the Tenancy is created; Reader memberships are created via the invitation flow.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. |
| **AccountId** | Foreign key to Account. |
| **Role** | Enumeration: Author or BetaReader. Immutable after creation. Exactly one Author-role membership per Tenancy. |
| **IsActive** | Boolean. False until the Account accepts their invitation (BetaReader) or until Tenancy creation completes (Author). The Author may set this false on a BetaReader membership to suspend access within the Tenancy. Restored by the Author at any time. |
| **IsSoftDeleted** | Boolean. Set true when the Author removes a reader from the Tenancy, or when the reader leaves the Tenancy. Does not affect the Account or any other membership. |
| **SoftDeletedAt** | Timestamp of membership soft deletion. Null if not deleted. |
| **RemovalInitiator** | Enumeration: Author or Member. Records which party initiated the membership soft deletion. Null if not deleted. Determines the reinstatement path. |
| **RemovedByAccountId** | Foreign key to Account. The Account that performed the soft deletion. Null if not deleted. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of membership creation (invitation issued or Tenancy created). |
| **ActivatedAt** | Timestamp when the BetaReader first accepted their invitation and became active. Null until activation or for Author memberships. |

## **3.5 DropboxConnection**

Stores the Dropbox integration credentials and configuration for a Tenancy. Each Tenancy has its own independent Dropbox connection. Credentials are held as opaque tokens managed through the abstract interface layer; no raw secrets are stored in the domain model.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. One-to-one. |
| **AccessToken** | Encrypted OAuth access token for the Tenancy owner's Dropbox account. Managed via the abstract credential store interface. |
| **RefreshToken** | Encrypted OAuth refresh token. Used to renew the access token without re-authorisation. |
| **TokenExpiresAt** | Timestamp when the current access token expires. The System refreshes automatically before expiry. |
| **AuthorisedAt** | Timestamp when the Tenancy owner last completed the Dropbox OAuth flow. |
| **Status** | Enumeration: Connected, TokenExpired, Revoked, Error. Reflects the current health of the connection. |
| **ErrorMessage** | Free text. Populated when Status is Error; null otherwise. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of connection record creation. |

## **3.6 Invitation**

Represents an invitation issued by the Author to a prospective beta reader within their Tenancy. A TenancyMembership record is created when the invitation is issued. If no Account exists for the invited email, an Account record is also created at this point. The Invitation record tracks the lifecycle of that invitation.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. The Tenancy into which the reader is being invited. |
| **AccountId** | Foreign key to Account. The Account this invitation is for (created at invitation time if new). |
| **Token** | Cryptographically random string included in the invitation email link. Single-use. |
| **ExpiryPolicy** | Enumeration: AlwaysOpen or ExpiresAt. Set by the Author at time of issue. |
| **ExpiresAt** | Datetime. Populated when ExpiryPolicy is ExpiresAt; null when AlwaysOpen. |
| **Status** | Enumeration: Pending, Accepted, Cancelled, Expired. |
| **IsNewAccount** | Boolean. True if an Account was created as part of this invitation; false if the invited email matched an existing Account. |
| **IssuedAt** | Timestamp of invitation creation. |
| **AcceptedAt** | Timestamp when the Account holder clicked the link and activated. Null until accepted. |
| **CancelledAt** | Timestamp when the Author cancelled the invitation. Null unless cancelled. |

## **3.7 ScrivenerProject**

Represents a single Scrivener .scriv project folder synced via the Tenancy's registered Dropbox connection. Always scoped to one Tenancy.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. |
| **Name** | Human-readable project name, sourced from the Scrivener project title. |
| **DropboxPath** | Absolute path to the .scriv folder within the Tenancy's connected Dropbox volume. |
| **IsReaderActive** | Boolean. When true, beta readers can see published sections in this project. At most one project per Tenancy may have this true at any time. Controlled explicitly by the Author. |
| **ReaderActivatedAt** | Timestamp when IsReaderActive was most recently set true. Null if never activated. |
| **LastSyncedAt** | Timestamp of the most recent successful parse by the System actor. |
| **SyncStatus** | Enumeration: Healthy, Stale, Error. |
| **SyncErrorMessage** | Free text. Populated when SyncStatus is Error; null otherwise. |
| **IsSoftDeleted** | Boolean. Soft-deleted projects are hidden from readers and excluded from all active processing. |
| **SoftDeletedAt** | Timestamp of soft deletion. Null if not deleted. |

## **3.8 Section**

Represents a single node in the Scrivener binder — a folder (grouping node) or a document (prose unit backed by an RTF file). The tree structure mirrors the Scrivener binder exactly. Sections removed from the binder are soft-deleted; their comments are preserved.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **ProjectId** | Foreign key to ScrivenerProject. |
| **ScrivenerUuid** | The UUID assigned by Scrivener, stable across renames. Used to reconcile sync updates. Unique within a project. |
| **ParentId** | Foreign key to Section. Null for root-level nodes. No cycles permitted. |
| **Title** | Section title as shown in the Scrivener binder. |
| **SortOrder** | Integer. Defines display order among siblings. |
| **NodeType** | Enumeration: Folder or Document. |
| **ScrivenerStatus** | The status label as set in Scrivener. Free text mirrored from the project file. |
| **HtmlContent** | Prose content converted from RTF to HTML by the sync process. Null for Folder nodes. |
| **IsPublished** | Boolean. True when the Author has explicitly made this section available to beta readers. Only Document nodes may be published. |
| **PublishedAt** | Timestamp of the most recent publish action. Null if never published. |
| **UnpublishedAt** | Timestamp of the most recent unpublish action. Null if never unpublished. |
| **ContentHash** | Hash of the RTF source at last sync. Used to detect content drift since publication. |
| **ContentChangedSincePublish** | Boolean. True when the current ContentHash differs from the hash captured at the most recent publish action. |
| **IsSoftDeleted** | Boolean. True when the section has been removed from the Scrivener binder. |
| **SoftDeletedAt** | Timestamp of soft deletion. Null if not deleted. |

## **3.9 Comment**

Represents a single message in a comment thread attached to a Section. Comments form a tree via ParentCommentId. There is no depth limit. Soft-deleted comments are retained; their body is replaced with a tombstone placeholder for readers but remains visible to the Author.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **SectionId** | Foreign key to Section. |
| **AuthorAccountId** | Foreign key to Account. |
| **ParentCommentId** | Foreign key to Comment. Null for root comments. |
| **Body** | Comment text. Must not be empty or whitespace-only on any non-deleted comment. |
| **Visibility** | Enumeration: Public or Private. Immutable after creation. Inherited by all replies when the root is Private. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of creation. |
| **EditedAt** | Timestamp of most recent edit. Null if never edited. |
| **IsSoftDeleted** | Boolean. Soft-delete flag. |
| **SoftDeletedAt** | Timestamp of soft deletion. Null if not deleted. |

## **3.10 ReadEvent**

Records each time a beta reader opens a section. Multiple opens of the same section by the same reader update LastOpenedAt only; FirstOpenedAt is immutable after creation.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **SectionId** | Foreign key to Section. |
| **AccountId** | Foreign key to Account. |
| **FirstOpenedAt** | Timestamp of the first open. Set on creation, never updated. |
| **LastOpenedAt** | Timestamp of the most recent open. Updated on every subsequent open. |
| **OpenCount** | Integer. Incremented on every open. Minimum value of 1. |

## **3.11 UserBlock**

Records a platform-wide block between two Accounts. A block is owned by the blocking Account and applies across all Tenancies and all future platform contexts. Blocks are independent — either party may block the other separately, resulting in two records for the same pair. A block does not automatically affect Tenancy membership; membership removal remains a separate explicit action.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **BlockingAccountId** | Foreign key to Account. The Account initiating the block. |
| **BlockedAccountId** | Foreign key to Account. The Account being blocked. Must differ from BlockingAccountId. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of block creation. |

## **3.12 UserNotificationPreferences**

Stores notification preferences for an Account within a specific Tenancy. One record per (Account, Tenancy) pair, created with default values when a TenancyMembership is created.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **AccountId** | Foreign key to Account. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. |
| **NotifyOnNewSection** | Boolean. Reader receives email when a new section is published on the reader-active project, provided the caught-up condition is met. |
| **NotifyOnSectionChanged** | Boolean. Reader opt-in to receive email when a previously-read section's content changes after re-publish. |
| **NotifyOnReply** | Enumeration: Never, AuthorOnly, AnyParticipant. Controls when the reader is notified of replies to threads they participate in. |
| **AuthorDigestMode** | Enumeration: Immediate, Digest. Author-only field. Controls comment notification batching. Null for BetaReader memberships. |
| **AuthorDigestIntervalHours** | Integer. Author-only. Batch interval in hours when AuthorDigestMode is Digest. Null otherwise. |
| **AuthorTimezone** | IANA timezone string. Author-only. Used to schedule digest delivery. Null for BetaReader memberships. |

## **3.13 EmailDeliveryLog**

Records every email dispatch attempt made by the system within a Tenancy. Used to surface delivery failures on the Author dashboard and to support retry logic.

| **Property** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| **Id** | Unique identifier. System-assigned. |
| **TenancyId** | Foreign key to Tenancy. Scopes the log to the originating Tenancy. |
| **RecipientAccountId** | Foreign key to Account. |
| **RecipientEmail** | The email address used at time of send. Captured in case the Account's address changes later. |
| **EmailType** | Enumeration: Invitation, CommentNotification, ReplyNotification, NewSectionNotification, SectionChangedNotification, DigestNotification. |
| **Status** | Enumeration: Pending, Sent, Failed, Retrying. |
| **AttemptCount** | Integer. Number of delivery attempts made. |
| **LastAttemptAt** | Timestamp of the most recent attempt. |
| **SentAt** | Timestamp of successful delivery confirmation. Null until delivered. |
| **FailureReason** | Free text. Populated on failure; null otherwise. |
| **RelatedEntityId** | Optional reference to the Comment, Section, or other entity that triggered this email. Nullable. |
| **CreatedAt** | Timestamp of log record creation. |

# **4. Relationships**

| **Relationship** | **Cardinality and Notes** |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Account → TenancyMembership | One-to-many. An Account may hold memberships across many Tenancies. |  |
| Account → UserBlock | One-to-many (as blocker). Blocks are platform-wide and not scoped to any Tenancy. |  |
| Tenancy → TenancyMembership | One-to-many. Exactly one membership with Role = Author per Tenancy. |  |
| Tenancy → TenancySubscription | One-to-one. |  |
| Tenancy → DropboxConnection | One-to-one. Each Tenancy has its own independent Dropbox connection. |  |
| Tenancy → ScrivenerProject | One-to-many. |  |
| Tenancy → Invitation | One-to-many. Invitations are scoped to the issuing Tenancy. |  |
| TenancyMembership → Invitation | One-to-one. Each BetaReader membership has exactly one Invitation record. |  |
| TenancyMembership → UserNotificationPreferences | One-to-one. Created with default values when the membership is created. |  |
| ScrivenerProject → Section | One-to-many. Sections are soft-deleted when removed from the binder. |  |
| Section → Section | Self-referential one-to-many via ParentId. No cycles permitted. Soft-deleting a parent cascades soft-deletion to all descendants. |  |
| Section → Comment | One-to-many. A section may have many root comments. |  |
| Comment → Comment | Self-referential one-to-many via ParentCommentId. A reply must belong to the same section as its parent. |  |
| Account → Comment | One-to-many. An Account may author many comments across all Tenancies in which it holds membership. |  |
| Account → ReadEvent | One-to-many. An Account may have read events across many sections. |  |
| Section → ReadEvent | One-to-many. A section may have read events from many Accounts. Unique constraint on (SectionId, AccountId). |  |
| Account → EmailDeliveryLog | One-to-many (as recipient). All emails sent to an Account are logged. |  |

# **5. Enumerations**

| **Enumeration** | **Value** | **Meaning** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Role** | **Author** | The Account that owns the Tenancy. Exactly one per Tenancy. |
|  | **BetaReader** | An invited reader within a Tenancy. |
| **RemovalInitiator** | **Author** | The Tenancy Author initiated the membership removal. |
|  | **Member** | The member themselves initiated departure from the Tenancy. |
| **SubscriptionTier** | **Free** | Up to 3 beta readers, 1 active project. |
|  | **Paid** | Up to 10 beta readers, unlimited active projects. |
|  | **Ultimate** | Unlimited beta readers and projects. |
| **SubscriptionStatus** | **Active** | Subscription is current and in good standing. |
|  | **Suspended** | Access suspended; signalled by external billing system. |
|  | **Cancelled** | Subscription cancelled; Tenancy enters read-only or wind-down state. |
| **DropboxConnectionStatus** | **Connected** | OAuth token valid; sync operational. |
|  | **TokenExpired** | Access token has expired; refresh required. |
|  | **Revoked** | Owner revoked access in Dropbox; re-authorisation required. |
|  | **Error** | Connection error. ErrorMessage populated. |
| **NodeType** | **Folder** | Binder grouping node. No prose. Cannot be published. |
|  | **Document** | Prose unit backed by an RTF file. Unit of publication and commentary. |
| **Visibility** | **Public** | Visible to the Author and all readers with access to the parent section. |
|  | **Private** | Visible only to the Author and the comment's own author. |
| **SyncStatus** | **Healthy** | Last sync completed without error. |
|  | **Stale** | Project file older than configured threshold or polling window missed. |
|  | **Error** | Parse failed. SyncErrorMessage populated. |
| **ExpiryPolicy** | **AlwaysOpen** | Invitation never expires. |
|  | **ExpiresAt** | Invitation expires at the datetime in ExpiresAt. |
| **InvitationStatus** | **Pending** | Issued, not yet accepted or cancelled. |
|  | **Accepted** | Account holder clicked the link and activated. |
|  | **Cancelled** | Author cancelled before acceptance. |
|  | **Expired** | ExpiryPolicy was ExpiresAt and the expiry datetime passed without acceptance. |
| **NotifyOnReply** | **Never** | No reply notifications sent. |
|  | **AuthorOnly** | Notified only when the Author role replies to their thread. |
|  | **AnyParticipant** | Notified when any participant replies to a thread they are in. |
| **AuthorDigestMode** | **Immediate** | One email sent per comment event. |
|  | **Digest** | Comments batched and sent as a single digest at the configured interval. |
| **EmailType** | **Invitation** | Account invitation email. |
|  | **CommentNotification** | Author notified of a new comment. |
|  | **ReplyNotification** | Reader notified of a reply. |
|  | **NewSectionNotification** | Reader notified of a newly published section. |
|  | **SectionChangedNotification** | Reader notified of changed section content. |
|  | **DigestNotification** | Author digest batch email. |
| **EmailStatus** | **Pending** | Queued, not yet attempted. |
|  | **Sent** | Delivered successfully. |
|  | **Failed** | All retry attempts exhausted. |
|  | **Retrying** | Failed at least once, retry pending. |

# **6. Business Rules**

## **6.1 Deployment and Platform Independence**

- The system has no dependency on any specific cloud provider, operating system, or hosting platform.

- All external service interactions — email, file system, Dropbox, database — are accessed through interfaces defined in the domain layer. Concrete implementations are injected at runtime via configuration.

- Configuration is supplied via environment variables or a platform-neutral configuration file. No connection strings, API keys, or provider names are hardcoded.

## **6.2 Multi-Tenancy and Isolation Rules**

- Every ScrivenerProject, Section, Comment, Invitation, Membership, and EmailDeliveryLog record belongs to exactly one Tenancy.

- No data belonging to one Tenancy is accessible to the Author or readers of another Tenancy.

- A Tenancy's data isolation boundary is enforced at the domain layer; it is not a database-only concern.

- An Account may own at most one Tenancy.

- An Account may hold BetaReader memberships in any number of Tenancies simultaneously. Activity in one Tenancy has no effect on membership or standing in another.

- The System actor may only operate on a Tenancy whose DropboxConnection has Status = Connected.

## **6.3 Account and Identity Rules**

- An Account is the sole carrier of login credentials and DisplayName on the platform.

- DisplayName is owned by the Account holder. No Tenancy may set or override it.

- A change to DisplayName propagates immediately across all Tenancies and all historical comments.

- An Account is soft-deleted by the Account holder only. Platform-level soft deletion is not available to any Tenancy Author.

- When an Account is soft-deleted, all its TenancyMemberships become inert. The Account holder's comments are retained; their displayed name becomes 'Deleted Account' across all Tenancies.

- There is no limit on the number of Accounts on the platform.

## **6.4 Tenancy Membership Rules**

- Exactly one TenancyMembership with Role = Author exists per Tenancy.

- The Author membership may not be soft-deleted or deactivated.

- A TenancyMembership with Role = BetaReader may be soft-deleted by the Author (administrative removal) or by the member themselves (voluntary departure).

- When an Author removes a reader (RemovalInitiator = Author), the Author may reinstate the membership directly without a new invitation.

- When a member departs (RemovalInitiator = Member), reinstatement requires a new invitation issued by the Author and accepted by the member. The existing membership record is reactivated on acceptance.

- The Author may deactivate a BetaReader membership (IsActive = false) without soft-deleting it. Deactivated readers cannot log in to the Tenancy. The membership may be reactivated by the Author at any time.

## **6.5 Tombstone Display Rules**

- When rendering a comment author's name, the following precedence applies:

- (1) If Account.IsSoftDeleted is true: display 'Deleted Account' to all parties in all Tenancies.

- (2) If the relevant TenancyMembership.IsSoftDeleted is true: display 'Removed Member' to other readers within that Tenancy.

- (3) Otherwise: display Account.DisplayName.

- The Tenancy Author always sees the real DisplayName and the original comment body, regardless of deletion or removal status.

- Readers see tombstone labels but never the original body of a soft-deleted comment.

## **6.6 Block Rules**

- Any Account may block any other Account. A block is platform-wide and applies across all Tenancies and future platform contexts.

- Blocks are independent. Either party may block the other separately. Two block records may exist for the same pair.

- When a block exists in either direction between two Accounts, neither party sees the other's comments, profile, or activity on any shared section.

- A block does not automatically affect TenancyMembership. The Author may block a reader as a personal act while the reader retains their membership; the Author must separately remove the membership if they wish to revoke access.

- An Account may not block itself.

## **6.7 Dropbox Connection Rules**

- Each Tenancy has exactly one DropboxConnection record.

- Dropbox credentials are stored as encrypted tokens via the abstract credential store interface. No raw OAuth secrets are held in the domain layer.

- The System may only sync a project when its Tenancy's DropboxConnection has Status = Connected.

- Token refresh is handled automatically by the System before expiry. If refresh fails, Status transitions to TokenExpired and sync is suspended for that Tenancy.

- If the Account holder revokes access at the Dropbox level, Status transitions to Revoked. Re-authorisation requires the Tenancy owner to repeat the OAuth flow.

- DropboxPath on a ScrivenerProject is relative to the connected Dropbox account's root. It is scoped to the Tenancy's own connection and is not portable across Tenancies.

## **6.8 Project Activation Rules**

- At most one ScrivenerProject per Tenancy may have IsReaderActive = true at any time.

- The Author explicitly activates and deactivates projects. The System never changes IsReaderActive automatically.

- Activating a project automatically deactivates the previously active project within the same Tenancy, if any.

- An Author may publish sections on any project regardless of its IsReaderActive state.

- Beta readers may only see sections belonging to the currently reader-active project within their Tenancy.

- Deactivating a project immediately hides all its published sections from beta readers. IsPublished states on individual sections are not modified.

## **6.9 Publishing Rules**

- Only sections with NodeType = Document may be published.

- Publication is an explicit Author action. The System never auto-publishes.

- When the sync process updates a published section's content, it sets ContentChangedSincePublish = true and does not alter IsPublished. The Author decides whether to re-publish.

- The Author may unpublish a section at any time. Existing comments are retained but become inaccessible to beta readers until the section is re-published.

- Soft-deleted sections may not be published.

## **6.10 Comment Rules**

- Only authenticated Accounts with an active, non-deleted TenancyMembership may create comments within that Tenancy.

- Beta readers may only comment on sections that are published and belong to the reader-active project.

- The Author may comment on any section in their Tenancy regardless of published or active project status.

- A comment body must contain at least one non-whitespace character.

- A user may create multiple independent root comments on the same section.

- A reply must reference an existing, non-deleted comment as its parent and must belong to the same section.

- Visibility is immutable after creation. A Private root comment propagates Private visibility to all replies, regardless of the replying user's requested visibility.

- A user may edit their own comments. Editing updates Body and sets EditedAt. Soft-deleted comments may not be edited.

- A user may soft-delete their own comments. The Author may soft-delete any comment within their Tenancy. No comment data is ever physically deleted.

## **6.11 Visibility Rules**

- A Public comment is visible to the Author and all beta readers who can access the parent section, subject to block rules.

- A Private comment is visible only to its author and the Tenancy Author.

- A beta reader may not see the count, content, or existence of private comments authored by other beta readers.

- The Tenancy Author sees all comments — public and private — on all sections.

## **6.12 Reading Progress Rules**

- A ReadEvent is created the first time a beta reader opens a section. Subsequent opens update LastOpenedAt and increment OpenCount; FirstOpenedAt is never modified.

- There is exactly one ReadEvent record per (SectionId, AccountId) pair.

- A reader is considered caught up on a project when they have a ReadEvent for every currently published, non-soft-deleted Document section in that project.

- The caught-up check is per-project within a Tenancy.

- Content changes to a section after first open do not invalidate the existing ReadEvent.

## **6.13 Invitation and Account Rules**

- Only the Tenancy Author may issue invitations within their Tenancy.

- An invitation creates an inactive TenancyMembership. If no Account exists for the invited email, an Account record is also created at this point.

- For an existing Account accepting a new Tenancy invitation, only a new TenancyMembership is created; no Account-level data is changed.

- Clicking the invitation link is the single activation step. For a new Account, the holder sets their DisplayName and password. For an existing Account, this step is skipped and they proceed directly into the Tenancy.

- An expired or cancelled invitation link is rejected. The Author must issue a new invitation.

- The Author may cancel a Pending invitation. Cancellation does not delete the Account or TenancyMembership.

- There is exactly one Author TenancyMembership per Tenancy. The system does not permit creation of a second Author-role membership within the same Tenancy.

## **6.14 Subscription and Tier Rules**

- Each Tenancy has exactly one TenancySubscription record.

- Tier limits (reader count, active project count) are enforced at the Tenancy level.

- An Account that is a BetaReader only, with no Tenancy of their own, has no financial obligations to the platform.

- Financial obligation attaches to the Account that holds the Author membership for a Tenancy.

- Tier assignment is developer-managed in Phase 1. Rules for over-limit behaviour on downgrade are deferred.

## **6.15 Notification Rules**

- Notification preferences are stored per (Account, Tenancy) in UserNotificationPreferences. They are scoped to the Tenancy and do not affect the Account's notifications in other Tenancies.

- Author — new comment: the Author is notified when any beta reader creates a root comment or reply. Delivery mode is controlled by AuthorDigestMode.

- Beta reader — reply notification: a reader is notified of replies per their NotifyOnReply preference.

- Beta reader — new section: a reader is notified when a new section is published on the reader-active project, provided NotifyOnNewSection is true and they are caught up.

- Beta reader — section changed: a reader is notified when a section they have previously opened changes after re-publish, provided NotifyOnSectionChanged is true.

- Every email dispatch attempt is recorded in EmailDeliveryLog. Failed deliveries are surfaced on the Author dashboard. Retry behaviour is implementation-defined.

- Blocks are respected by the notification system. No notification is sent to an Account about activity originating from an Account they have blocked, or that has blocked them.

## **6.16 Data Retention Rules**

- No data is ever physically deleted from the system.

- All deletions are soft: IsSoftDeleted is set true and SoftDeletedAt is recorded.

- Soft-deleted entities are excluded from all normal queries but remain accessible to the Author and to the System for audit purposes.

# **7. Domain Services**

## **7.1 SyncService**

- ParseProject(tenancyId, projectId) — Validates the Tenancy's DropboxConnection is Connected. Reads project.scrivx, walks the binder tree, creates or updates Section records, soft-deletes records for nodes no longer present. Updates LastSyncedAt and SyncStatus.

- DetectContentChanges(tenancyId, projectId) — Compares ContentHash of all published sections against current RTF source. Sets ContentChangedSincePublish where drift is detected. Triggers SectionChangedNotification for eligible readers.

- RefreshDropboxToken(tenancyId) — Obtains a new access token using the stored refresh token. Updates DropboxConnection.AccessToken and TokenExpiresAt. Sets Status to TokenExpired on failure.

## **7.2 TenancyService**

- CreateTenancy(accountId, name) — Creates a Tenancy record, an Author TenancyMembership, a TenancySubscription (Free tier), a DropboxConnection stub, and a UserNotificationPreferences record for the owner.

- RegisterDropboxConnection(tenancyId, authorId, oauthCode) — Exchanges the OAuth code for access and refresh tokens. Stores encrypted tokens. Sets DropboxConnection.Status = Connected.

- GetTenancyForAccount(accountId) — Returns the Tenancy owned by the given Account, or null if they do not own one.

## **7.3 ProjectService**

- ActivateForReaders(tenancyId, projectId, authorId) — Validates the acting Account holds the Author membership for the Tenancy. Deactivates any currently active project in the Tenancy. Sets IsReaderActive = true on the target project.

- DeactivateForReaders(tenancyId, projectId, authorId) — Sets IsReaderActive = false. Does not alter section publish states.

- GetReaderActiveProject(tenancyId) — Returns the single project with IsReaderActive = true for the Tenancy, or null.

## **7.4 PublicationService**

- Publish(tenancyId, sectionId, authorId) — Validates the section is a non-deleted Document within the Tenancy. Sets IsPublished = true, records PublishedAt, captures ContentHash, clears ContentChangedSincePublish. Triggers NewSectionNotification for caught-up readers if the project is reader-active.

- Unpublish(tenancyId, sectionId, authorId) — Sets IsPublished = false, records UnpublishedAt.

- GetPublishedSections(tenancyId, projectId) — Returns all non-deleted Document sections with IsPublished = true for the given project.

## **7.5 CommentService**

- CreateRootComment(tenancyId, sectionId, accountId, body, visibility) — Validates the Account may comment in the Tenancy on the section. Creates a Comment. Triggers CommentNotification to the Author.

- CreateReply(tenancyId, parentCommentId, accountId, body, requestedVisibility) — Validates the parent exists and is not deleted. Enforces visibility inheritance. Creates the reply. Triggers ReplyNotification and CommentNotification as appropriate. Respects block rules when dispatching notifications.

- EditComment(tenancyId, commentId, accountId, newBody) — Validates ownership and non-deleted status. Updates Body and EditedAt.

- SoftDeleteComment(tenancyId, commentId, actingAccountId) — Validates the actor is the comment author or holds the Author membership for the Tenancy. Sets IsSoftDeleted = true.

- GetThreadsForSection(tenancyId, sectionId, requestingAccountId) — Returns all root comments with their reply trees, filtered by visibility rules and block rules for the requesting Account.

## **7.6 ReadingProgressService**

- RecordOpen(tenancyId, sectionId, accountId) — Creates a ReadEvent if none exists for the pair, or updates LastOpenedAt and increments OpenCount.

- IsCaughtUp(tenancyId, accountId, projectId) — Returns true if the Account has a ReadEvent for every published non-deleted Document section in the project.

- GetProgressForProject(tenancyId, projectId) — Returns per-reader, per-section read status for all published sections. Used by the Author dashboard.

## **7.7 MembershipService**

- IssueInvitation(tenancyId, email, expiryPolicy, expiresAt, authorId) — Validates the acting Account holds the Author membership. Checks whether an Account exists for the email; creates one if not. Creates a TenancyMembership and Invitation record. Dispatches an invitation email.

- AcceptInvitation(token, displayName, password) — Validates the token is Pending and not expired. For new Accounts: sets DisplayName and hashed password, marks Account active. For existing Accounts: skips credential setup. Activates the TenancyMembership, marks Invitation Accepted.

- CancelInvitation(tenancyId, invitationId, authorId) — Validates the invitation is Pending. Sets Status = Cancelled.

- DeactivateMembership(tenancyId, targetAccountId, authorId) — Sets IsActive = false on the target membership. Author membership may not be deactivated.

- ReactivateMembership(tenancyId, targetAccountId, authorId) — Sets IsActive = true on the target membership.

- RemoveMember(tenancyId, targetAccountId, authorId) — Sets TenancyMembership.IsSoftDeleted = true, RemovalInitiator = Author. Author membership may not be removed.

- LeaveTenancy(tenancyId, accountId) — Sets TenancyMembership.IsSoftDeleted = true, RemovalInitiator = Member. Cannot be used by the Author on their own membership.

- ReinstateMember(tenancyId, targetAccountId, authorId) — Valid only when RemovalInitiator = Author. Sets IsSoftDeleted = false, clears removal fields.

## **7.8 BlockService**

- BlockAccount(blockingAccountId, blockedAccountId) — Validates the two IDs differ and no existing block record exists for the pair in this direction. Creates a UserBlock record.

- UnblockAccount(blockingAccountId, blockedAccountId) — Removes the UserBlock record. (Physical deletion is permitted here as block records carry no dependent data and no audit requirement.)

- IsBlocked(accountIdA, accountIdB) — Returns true if a UserBlock exists in either direction between the two Accounts.

## **7.9 AccountService**

- DeleteAccount(accountId) — Account holder action. Sets Account.IsSoftDeleted = true and SoftDeletedAt. All TenancyMemberships become inert. Cannot be performed by any Tenancy Author on behalf of another Account.

- UpdateDisplayName(accountId, newDisplayName) — Sets Account.DisplayName. Change propagates immediately across all Tenancies and historical comment rendering.

- UpdateEmail(accountId, newEmail) — Validates the new email is unique across the platform. Updates Account.Email.

## **7.10 NotificationService**

- SendImmediate(tenancyId, emailType, recipientAccountId, relatedEntityId) — Constructs and dispatches a single notification email. Respects block rules. Records attempt in EmailDeliveryLog.

- SendDigest(tenancyId, authorId) — Collects all unsent comment notifications since the last digest for the Tenancy. Constructs and dispatches a single digest email. Records attempt.

- RetryFailed(tenancyId) — Identifies EmailDeliveryLog records within the Tenancy with Status = Failed or Retrying within retry policy. Reattempts delivery.

- GetDeliveryFailures(tenancyId) — Returns all EmailDeliveryLog records with Status = Failed for the Tenancy, for display on the Author dashboard.

## **7.11 DashboardService**

- GetProjectOverview(tenancyId, projectId, authorId) — Returns per-section comment counts, publish status, content-changed flags, and per-reader read status for all published sections.

- GetReaderSummary(tenancyId, authorId) — Returns all BetaReader memberships with their active/deleted status, caught-up status per project, and comment counts.

- GetEmailHealthSummary(tenancyId, authorId) — Returns counts of Pending, Sent, Failed, and Retrying emails, with detail on Failed records, scoped to the Tenancy.

# **8. Invariants**

The following conditions must hold at all times. Any operation that would violate an invariant must be rejected before persistence.

| **ID** | **Statement** |
| --- | --- |
| **I-01** | Exactly one TenancyMembership with Role = Author exists per Tenancy. |
| **I-02** | At most one ScrivenerProject per Tenancy has IsReaderActive = true at any time. |
| **I-03** | A Comment's SectionId always matches the SectionId of its parent comment, when a parent exists. |
| **I-04** | A Comment with a private parent comment always has Visibility = Private. |
| **I-05** | Only sections with NodeType = Document may have IsPublished = true. |
| **I-06** | A Section with IsPublished = true must have a non-null PublishedAt timestamp. |
| **I-07** | A soft-deleted entity must have a non-null SoftDeletedAt timestamp. |
| **I-08** | Comment.Body must not be null, empty, or whitespace-only on any non-soft-deleted comment. |
| **I-09** | ScrivenerUuid must be unique within a given ScrivenerProject. |
| **I-10** | A Section's ParentId may not reference itself, directly or transitively (no cycles in the section tree). |
| **I-11** | There is at most one ReadEvent record per (SectionId, AccountId) pair. |
| **I-12** | ReadEvent.FirstOpenedAt is immutable after creation. |
| **I-13** | ReadEvent.OpenCount is always >= 1. |
| **I-14** | There is exactly one UserNotificationPreferences record per TenancyMembership. |
| **I-15** | An Invitation token may only be used once. Once Accepted, the token is consumed. |
| **I-16** | The Author TenancyMembership may not have IsActive = false or IsSoftDeleted = true. |
| **I-17** | A Comment with IsSoftDeleted = true may not be the parent of a new reply. |
| **I-18** | A soft-deleted Section may not have IsPublished = true. |
| **I-19** | UserNotificationPreferences.AuthorDigestMode, AuthorDigestIntervalHours, and AuthorTimezone must be null for any TenancyMembership with Role = BetaReader. |
| **I-20** | An Account may own at most one Tenancy (at most one TenancyMembership with Role = Author across all Tenancies). |
| **I-21** | UserBlock.BlockingAccountId must not equal UserBlock.BlockedAccountId. |
| **I-22** | There is at most one UserBlock record per (BlockingAccountId, BlockedAccountId) pair. |
| **I-23** | Each Tenancy has exactly one DropboxConnection record. |
| **I-24** | Each Tenancy has exactly one TenancySubscription record. |
| **I-25** | TenancyMembership.RemovalInitiator and RemovedByAccountId must be null if and only if IsSoftDeleted is false. |
| **I-26** | An Account with IsSoftDeleted = true may not have IsActive = true on any TenancyMembership. |
| **I-27** | A TenancyMembership's TenancyId must match the TenancyId of the Invitation it is linked to, where applicable. |
| **I-28** | ScrivenerProject.DropboxPath is scoped to the Tenancy's own DropboxConnection and must not reference paths from another Tenancy's connection. |

# **9. Deferred and Out of Scope**

## **9.1 Phase 2 — Scrivener Write-back**

- Mapping accepted comments to Scrivener RTF annotations.

- Safe write-window strategy to prevent file contention with open Scrivener projects.

- Round-trip RTF preservation.

## **9.2 Subscription and Billing**

A tiered subscription model is in scope for a future phase. Current tier definitions:

| **Tier** | **Beta Readers** | **Active Projects** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Free | 3 | 1 |
| Paid | 10 | Unlimited |
| Ultimate | Unlimited | Unlimited |

Tier assignment is developer-managed in Phase 1. Rules for over-limit behaviour on downgrade, project locking, and slot recovery are deferred. No payment processing entities are planned for the system; subscription management is external.

## **9.3 Reader Community**

- Cross-tenancy reader identity features: shared reputation, public reader profiles, cross-author reading history.

- Reader-to-reader interaction beyond visibility of public comments on shared sections.

- The Account / TenancyMembership split in this version is designed to accommodate community features without structural change when that phase is reached.

## **9.4 Other Deferred Items**

- Notification model for admin/developer-facing alerts.

- Section access control at reader level (currently all-or-nothing per project).

- Section version history — retaining prior HTML snapshots across re-publishes.

- Comment export to document format.

- Admin interface for tier and system management.

- Tenancy ownership transfer.

- Multiple Scrivener projects synced from the same Dropbox path.